# Repo-root .vercelignore.
#
# DO NOT add `api` (or `api/`) here. Vercel applies this repo-root .vercelignore
# to the WHOLE-repo source upload for EVERY project built from this repo —
# including the API project, whose Root Directory is `api/`. Excluding `api`
# therefore strips the API project's own source during its cloud git build,
# which then fails instantly with no logs (the build dir is empty). This is NOT
# the same as local `vercel build`, which applies the ignore relative to the
# Root Directory — hence it only bites in the cloud. See PR #324.
#
# The static-frontend project (Root Directory = repo root) does NOT build api/
# as serverless functions anyway — verified: /api/* returns 404 on the SPA
# deploy — so excluding it was unnecessary as well as harmful.
#
# (Intentionally no ignore patterns below.)
